---
import TrustPageShell from '../components/public/TrustPageShell.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | CryptoPayMap"
  description="What CryptoPayMap is, what it publishes, and how its discovery, data, verification, and change surfaces fit together."
>
  <TrustPageShell
    eyebrow="Project"
    title="About CryptoPayMap"
    description="CryptoPayMap is a verification-focused discovery service for physical places and online services where a customer can attempt cryptocurrency payment at checkout."
  >
    <div class="grid gap-8">
      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5 shadow-sm sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">What the product is for</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          A useful listing should answer practical payment questions before a customer attempts a purchase: which asset is accepted, which network is required, whether the payment is direct or processor-assisted, how the checkout works, what evidence supports the record, and when it was last confirmed.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          CryptoPayMap is not a generic directory of businesses described as “crypto friendly.” Public discovery is built from reviewed records with explicit payment details and status.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Two discovery surfaces</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5">
            <h3 class="m-0 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Places</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">
              Physical locations use a coordinated map and list. Confirmed records are shown by default, with filters for payment details and an explicit Search this area action after map movement.
            </p>
            <a class="mt-3 inline-flex min-h-11 items-center font-semibold text-brand-700" href="/places">
              Browse Places
            </a>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5">
            <h3 class="m-0 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Online Services</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">
              Online acceptance is presented separately because checkout scope, products, renewals, regions, and processor routes differ from physical-location acceptance.
            </p>
            <a class="mt-3 inline-flex min-h-11 items-center font-semibold text-brand-700" href="/online">
              Browse Online Services
            </a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-brand-50 p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Public information has separate roles</h2>
        <dl class="mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-ink">Stats</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Describes the current published dataset and its quality and coverage.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-ink">Updates</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Shows reviewed changes to public acceptance records.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-ink">Roadmap</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Describes future product capabilities using Now, Next, Later, and Exploring.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-ink">Changelog</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">Records released product, interface, policy, and public data-contract changes.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Integrity boundaries</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 grid list-disc gap-2 pl-5 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          <li>Candidate records remain private and do not appear in public maps, search, or Stats.</li>
          <li>Verification status is independent from sponsorship, advertising, payment, or partnership relationships.</li>
          <li>User submissions do not update canonical public records automatically.</li>
          <li>Public exports exclude private review material, restricted evidence, and personal information.</li>
          <li>Map interaction always has a list-based alternative.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 border-t border-border pt-6">
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control bg-brand-600 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-white no-underline hover:bg-brand-700" href="/methodology">
          Read the methodology
        </a>
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control border border-border px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-ink no-underline hover:bg-brand-50" href="/data">
          Explore public data
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </TrustPageShell>
</BaseLayout>
